![high](https://www.gstatic.com/codereviewagent/high-priority.svg)

The `sanitizeForWrapper` function unconditionally strips newlines, which is appropriate for tool-generated data per the 'secure by default' rule, but it breaks the formatting of multiline user inputs. Specifically, `formatUserHintsForModel` (which calls `wrapInput`) relies on newlines to present a list of hints to the model. When these newlines are replaced by spaces, the list structure is lost, potentially confusing the model.

I suggest making newline stripping optional in `sanitizeForWrapper` and disabling it for `wrapInput`, while keeping it enabled for `wrapBackgroundOutput` to satisfy the security requirement for tool data.

```suggestion
function sanitizeForWrapper(input: string, options: { stripNewlines?: boolean } = {}): string {
  const { stripNewlines = true } = options;
  const sanitized = input
    .replace(XML_CLOSING_TAG_RE, '<\\/$1>')
    .replace(CONTEXT_BREAKER_RE, '');
  return stripNewlines ? sanitized.replace(NEWLINE_RE, ' ') : sanitized;
}

function wrapInput(input: string): string {
  return '<user_input>\\n' + sanitizeForWrapper(input, { stripNewlines: false }) + '\\n</user_input>';
}

function wrapBackgroundOutput(input: string): string {
  return '<background_output>\\n' + sanitizeForWrapper(input, { stripNewlines: true }) + '\\n</background_output>';
}
```

